{"type":"message","id":"54647646","parentId":"91c0af4e","timestamp":"2026-07-11T19:55:14.160Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_917827a874f149da8aecdbd8","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"POST_TEXT='𝗛𝗮𝗹𝗳 𝗼𝗳 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗱 𝗮𝗻 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘁𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗽𝗮𝘀𝘀𝗲𝗱 𝗮𝗹𝗹 𝘁𝗲𝘀𝘁𝘀 — 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗳𝗮𝗶𝗹𝗲𝗱 𝗰𝘂𝘀𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗲𝗿𝘀.\n\nThe evaluation gap is real: AI agents are gaining autonomy faster than companies can verify them.\n\nThe data:\n→ 66% allow production deployment without human review — or are building toward it\n→ Only 5% fully trust the automated evaluations making those decisions\n→ 29% say the #1 weakness is poor alignment with real-world outcomes\n\nHere'\\''s the trap: A passing test doesn'\\''t mean a working agent. It means the agent succeeded once. It doesn'\\''t mean it succeeds every time.\n\nThe fix isn'\\''t slowing down. It'\\''s testing differently:\n→ Run the same scenario multiple times\n→ Vary phrasing and context\n→ Inject tool failures\n→ Turn every production incident into a permanent regression test\n\nRepeatability is the metric that matters. Not capability — consistency.\n\nYour agent can do the job once. Can it do it a thousand times without breaking?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #Testing #EnterpriseAI #Reliability'\n\n/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-publish/li-post.sh 264468965 \"$POST_TEXT\" /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/boring-agents-1783699220.png","timeout":60},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"POST_TEXT='𝗛𝗮𝗹𝗳 𝗼𝗳 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗱 𝗮𝗻 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘁𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗽𝗮𝘀𝘀𝗲𝗱 𝗮𝗹𝗹 𝘁𝗲𝘀𝘁𝘀 — 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗳𝗮𝗶𝗹𝗲𝗱 𝗰𝘂𝘀𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗲𝗿𝘀.\\n\\nThe evaluation gap is real: AI agents are gaining autonomy faster than companies can verify them.\\n\\nThe data:\\n→ 66% allow production deployment without human review — or are building toward it\\n→ Only 5% fully trust the automated evaluations making those decisions\\n→ 29% say the #1 weakness is poor alignment with real-world outcomes\\n\\nHere'\\\\''s the trap: A passing test doesn'\\\\''t mean a working agent. It means the agent