{"type":"message","id":"937e79e5","parentId":"30891035","timestamp":"2026-07-11T19:55:29.584Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Post published successfully."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_49feeac31a4b4a9dbb45a269","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts && cat > /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-11-ai-evaluation-gap.md << 'EOF'\n---\ndate: 2026-07-11T19:55:00Z\nlinkedin_url: https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7481798310014660608/\nimage: boring-agents-1783699220.png\nchars: 1199\ntags: [AI, AIAgents, Testing, EnterpriseAI, Reliability]\n---\n\n# AI Evaluation Gap\n\n𝗛𝗮𝗹𝗳 𝗼𝗳 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗱 𝗮𝗻 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘁𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗽𝗮𝘀𝘀𝗲𝗱 𝗮𝗹𝗹 𝘁𝗲𝘀𝘁𝘀 — 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗳𝗮𝗶𝗹𝗲𝗱 𝗰𝘂𝘀𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗲𝗿𝘀.\n\nThe evaluation gap is real: AI agents are gaining autonomy faster than companies can verify them.\n\nThe data:\n→ 66% allow production deployment without human review — or are building toward it\n→ Only 5% fully trust the automated evaluations making those decisions\n→ 29% say the #1 weakness is poor alignment with real-world outcomes\n\nHere's the trap: A passing test doesn't mean a working agent. It means the agent succeeded once. It doesn't mean it succeeds every time.\n\nThe fix isn't slowing down. It's testing differently:\n→ Run the same scenario multiple times\n→ Vary phrasing and context\n→ Inject tool failures\n→ Turn every production incident into a permanent regression test\n\nRepeatability is the metric that matters. Not capability — consistency.\n\nYour agent can do the job once. Can it do it a thousand times without breaking?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #Testing #EnterpriseAI #Reliability\nEOF\necho \"Post record saved.\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"mkdir -p /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts && cat > /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-11-ai-evaluation-gap.md << 'EOF'\\n---\\ndate: 2026-07-11T19:55:00Z\\nlinkedin_url: https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7481798310014660608/\\nimage: boring-agents-1783699220.png\\nchars: 1199\\ntags: [AI, AIAgents, Testing, EnterpriseAI, Reliability]\\n---\\n\\n# AI Evaluation Gap\\n\\n𝗛𝗮𝗹𝗳 𝗼𝗳 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗱 𝗮𝗻 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘁𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗽𝗮𝘀𝘀𝗲𝗱 𝗮𝗹𝗹 𝘁𝗲𝘀𝘁𝘀 — 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗳𝗮𝗶𝗹𝗲𝗱 𝗰𝘂𝘀𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗲𝗿𝘀.\\n\\nThe evaluation gap is real: AI agents are gaining autonomy faster than companies can verify them.\\n\\nThe data:\\n→ 66% allow production deployment without human review — or are building toward it\\n→ Only 5% fully trust the automated evaluations making those decisions\\n→ 29% say the #1 weakness is poor alignment with real-world outcomes\\n\\nHere's the trap: A passing test doesn't mean a working agent. It means the agent succeeded once. It doesn't mean it succeeds every time.\\n\\nThe fix isn't slowing down. It's testing differently:\\n→ Run the same scenario multiple times\\n→ Vary phrasing and context\\n→ Inject tool failures\\n→ Turn every production incident into a permanent regression test\\n\\nRepeatability is the metric that matters. Not capability — consistency.\\n\\nYour agent can do the job once. Can it do it a thousand times without breaking?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #Testing #EnterpriseAI #Reliability\\nEOF\\necho \\\"Post record saved.\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783799722649,"responseId":"q59SavlHycPA5g-ypYuBBw"}}
